# Privacy Policy for Ultimate Switch

**Last Updated:** June 1, 2026

**Developer:** Charlie Fogg
**Contact:** charliefogg1@gmail.com

This Privacy Policy describes how Ultimate Switch ("the App," "we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, stores, and shares your information when you use our mobile application. By downloading, installing, or using Ultimate Switch, you agree to the practices described in this policy.

---

## 1. Information We Collect

### 1.1 Information You Provide

- **Display Name:** You may set a custom player name or use your Apple Game Center display name.
- **Customization Preferences:** Your chosen color theme, avatar, card back style, and win celebration effect.

### 1.2 Information Collected Automatically

- **Game Center Player ID:** When you sign in to Apple Game Center, we receive your Game Center player identifier to enable multiplayer features, leaderboards, and achievements.
- **Game Center Display Name and Profile Photo:** Retrieved from Apple Game Center to display your identity to other players during online matches.
- **Gameplay Statistics:** We automatically track gameplay data including games played, games won, rounds won, cards played, winning streaks, tournament results, XP earned, and player level.
- **Opponent Records:** We store head-to-head records against other players, including their Game Center player ID, display name, win/loss counts, and the date you last played together.
- **Session Data:** We store your most recent game session configuration (game mode, settings, and session type).

### 1.3 Information We Do Not Collect

We do not collect or access:

- Your real name, email address, phone number, or physical address
- Your precise or approximate location
- Your contacts, photos, camera, or microphone
- Device advertising identifiers (IDFA)
- Health, fitness, or biometric data
- Financial or payment information
- Browsing history or data from other apps

---

## 2. How We Use Your Information

We use the information described above for the following purposes:

- **Multiplayer Gameplay:** To match you with other players, display your identity in online matches, and transmit game state during play.
- **Leaderboards and Achievements:** To submit your player level and total XP to Apple Game Center leaderboards and to report achievement progress.
- **Friends and Social Features:** To load your Game Center friends list (with your permission) so you can invite friends to play and view who is available.
- **Statistics and Progress Tracking:** To display your gameplay history, win rates, achievement progress, XP history, and opponent records within the App.
- **Personalization:** To save and apply your customization preferences across sessions.
- **Live Activities:** To display current game state (current player name, card rank and suit, hand count, and game phase) on your Lock Screen and Dynamic Island during active games.

---

## 3. Third-Party Services

### 3.1 Apple Game Center (GameKit)

Ultimate Switch integrates with Apple Game Center to provide multiplayer matchmaking, leaderboards, achievements, and social features. When you use Game Center features, Apple processes your data in accordance with [Apple's Privacy Policy](https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/).

**Data shared with Apple Game Center:**

- Your Game Center player ID and display name
- Leaderboard scores (player level, total XP)
- Achievement unlock events
- Multiplayer match data (game moves, game state)

**Data accessed from Apple Game Center:**

- Your friends list (only when you grant permission)
- Your recent players list
- Your challengeable friends list
- Your profile photo

### 3.2 Firebase (Google Cloud) — Online Lobbies

Ultimate Switch may use Firebase, a Google Cloud platform service, to provide online lobby functionality. Firebase integration is optional and may not be active in all versions of the App. When active, Firebase processes data in accordance with [Google's Privacy Policy](https://policies.google.com/privacy).

**Data shared with Firebase:**

- An anonymous authentication identifier (no personal account required)
- Lobby information: player display names, Game Center player IDs, customization settings, game settings, and lobby status
- Lobby data is stored in Google Cloud Firestore

**Firebase does not receive:**

- Your real name, email, or any account credentials
- Your gameplay statistics or achievement data

### 3.3 No Other Third-Party Services

We do not integrate any advertising networks, analytics platforms, crash reporting services, or other third-party SDKs beyond those listed above.

---

## 4. Data Sharing and Disclosure

### 4.1 Shared with Other Players

During online multiplayer matches, the following information is visible to other players:

- Your display name
- Your Game Center player ID
- Your customization settings (color theme, avatar, card back style)
- Your game moves and actions during the match

### 4.2 Shared with Apple

Leaderboard scores, achievement progress, and multiplayer match data are shared with Apple through Game Center.

### 4.3 Shared with Google (When Firebase Is Active)

Online lobby data is stored in Google Cloud Firestore when Firebase integration is active.

### 4.4 No Sale of Data

**We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to any third party for any purpose.**

### 4.5 Legal Requirements

We may disclose your information if required to do so by law or in response to valid legal process, such as a court order or government request.

---

## 5. Data Storage and Security

### 5.1 Local Storage

The majority of your data is stored locally on your device using Apple's standard storage mechanisms (UserDefaults/AppStorage). This includes:

- Your display name and customization preferences
- All gameplay statistics, achievements, and opponent records
- Your cached Game Center display name
- Your most recent session configuration

### 5.2 Shared App Group Storage

The App uses an App Group container (`group.com.charliefogg.ultimateswitch`) to share limited game state data between the main app and the Live Activity widget extension. This data remains on your device.

### 5.3 Cloud Storage

- Game Center data (leaderboards, achievements, multiplayer) is stored on Apple's servers.
- Firebase lobby data (when active) is stored on Google Cloud servers.

### 5.4 Security

We rely on Apple's built-in platform security for local data storage and on Apple's and Google's enterprise-grade security infrastructure for cloud-stored data. We do not store sensitive credentials or personal account information.

---

## 6. Data Retention

- **Local Data:** Stored on your device indefinitely until you delete the App, reset your data within the App, or manually clear App data through your device settings.
- **XP History:** Automatically trimmed to a rolling one-year window.
- **Game Center Data:** Retained by Apple according to their data retention policies.
- **Firebase Lobby Data:** Lobby records are transient and associated with active game sessions. They are not retained after the lobby is closed.
- **Live Activity Data:** Automatically dismissed within seconds of a game ending and subject to a five-minute stale timeout.

---

## 7. Your Rights and Choices

### 7.1 Game Center

You can disable Game Center integration through your device's Settings app. This will disable multiplayer, leaderboards, achievements, and social features.

### 7.2 Friends List Access

The App requests permission to access your Game Center friends list. You can deny or revoke this permission at any time through your device's Settings app. Denying access will not affect core gameplay.

### 7.3 Data Deletion

You may delete all locally stored data by uninstalling the App from your device. To request deletion of your Game Center data (leaderboard scores, achievements), please contact Apple Support. To request deletion of any Firebase-stored data, please contact us at charliefogg1@gmail.com.

### 7.4 Rights Under GDPR (European Economic Area)

If you are located in the European Economic Area, you have the right to:

- **Access** the personal data we hold about you
- **Rectify** inaccurate personal data
- **Erase** your personal data ("right to be forgotten")
- **Restrict** or **object to** processing of your personal data
- **Data portability** — receive your data in a structured, machine-readable format
- **Withdraw consent** at any time where processing is based on consent

To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at charliefogg1@gmail.com. We will respond to your request within 30 days.

### 7.5 Rights Under CCPA (California)

If you are a California resident, you have the right to:

- **Know** what personal information we collect, use, and disclose
- **Delete** your personal information
- **Opt out** of the sale of your personal information (we do not sell personal information)
- **Non-discrimination** for exercising your privacy rights

To exercise these rights, please contact us at charliefogg1@gmail.com.

